{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:psalms.101",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 101,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 101 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:1",
      "text": "Song of a Psalm by David.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:2",
      "text": "Let them say so who have been redeemed by the Lord, whom he has redeemed from the hand of the enemy;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:3",
      "text": "and gathered them out of the countries, from the east, and west, and north, and",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:4",
      "text": "They wandered in the wilderness in a dry land; they found no way to a city of habitation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:5",
      "text": "Hungry and thirsty, their soul fainted in them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:6",
      "text": "Then they cried to the Lord in their affliction, and he delivered them out of their distresses.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:7",
      "text": "And he guided them into a straight path, that they might go to a city of habitation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:8",
      "text": "Let them acknowledge to the Lord his mercies, and his wonderful works to the children of men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:9",
      "text": "For he satisfies the empty soul, and fills the hungry soul with good things,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:10",
      "text": "even them that sit in darkness and the shadow of death, fettered in poverty and iron;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:11",
      "text": "because they rebelled against the words of God, and provoked the counsel of the Most High.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:12",
      "text": "So their heart was brought low with troubles; they were weak, and there was no helper.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:13",
      "text": "Then they cried to the Lord in their affliction, and he saved them out of their distresses.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:14",
      "text": "And he brought them out of darkness and the shadow of death, and broke their bonds asunder.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:15",
      "text": "Let them acknowledge to the Lord his mercies, and his wonders to the children of men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:16",
      "text": "For he broke to pieces the brazen gates, and crushed the iron bars.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:17",
      "text": "He helped them out of the way of their iniquity; for they were brought low because of their iniquities.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:18",
      "text": "Their soul abhorred all meat; and they drew near to the gates of death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:19",
      "text": "Then they cried to the Lord in their affliction, and he saved them out of their distresses.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:20",
      "text": "He sent his word, and healed them, and delivered them out of their destructions.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:21",
      "text": "Let them acknowledge to the Lord his mercies, and his wonderful works to the children of men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:22",
      "text": "And let them offer to him the sacrifice of praise, and proclaim his works with exultation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:23",
      "text": "They that go down to the sea in ships, doing business in many waters;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:24",
      "text": "these men have seen the works of the Lord, and his wonders in the deep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:25",
      "text": "He speaks, and the stormy wind arises, and its waves are lifted up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:26",
      "text": "They go up to the heavens, and go down to the depths; their soul melts because of troubles.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:27",
      "text": "They are troubled, they stagger as a drunkard, and all their wisdom is swallowed up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:28",
      "text": "Then they cry to the Lord in their affliction, and he brings them out of their distresses.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:29",
      "text": "And he commands the storm, and it is calmed into a gentle breeze, and its waves are still.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:30",
      "text": "And they are glad, because they are quiet; and he guides them to their desired haven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.31",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:31",
      "text": "Let them acknowledge to the Lord his mercies, and his wonderful works to the children of men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.32",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:32",
      "text": "Let them exalt him in the congregation of the people, and praise him in the seat of the elders.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.33",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:33",
      "text": "He turns rivers into a desert, and streams of water into a dry land;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.34",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:34",
      "text": "a fruitful land into saltness, for the wickedness of them that dwell in it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.35",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:35",
      "text": "He turns a wilderness into pools of water, and a dry land into streams of water.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.36",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:36",
      "text": "And there he causes the hungry to dwell, and they establish for themselves cities of habitation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.37",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:37",
      "text": "And they sow fields, and plant vineyards, and they yield fruit of increase.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.38",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:38",
      "text": "And he blesses them, and they multiply exceedingly, and he diminishes not the number of their cattle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.39",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:39",
      "text": "Again they become few, and are brought low, by the pressure of evils and pain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.40",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:40",
      "text": "Contempt is poured upon their princes, and he causes them to wander in a desert and trackless land.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.41",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:41",
      "text": "But he helps the poor out of poverty, and makes him families as a flock.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.42",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:42",
      "text": "The upright shall see and rejoice; and all iniquity shall stop her mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.43",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:43",
      "text": "Who is wise, and will observe these things, and understand the mercies of the Lord?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.44",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:44",
      "text": "Yet the Lord looked upon their affliction, when he heard their petition.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.45",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:45",
      "text": "And he remembered his covenant, and repented according to the multitude of his mercy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.46",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:46",
      "text": "And he caused them to be pitied in the sight of all who carried them captive.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.47",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:47",
      "text": "Save us, O Lord our God, and gather us from among the heathen, that we may give thanks to thy holy name, that we may glory in thy praise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.101.48",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 101,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 101:48",
      "text": "Blessed be the Lord God of Israel from everlasting and to everlasting; and all the people shall say, Amen, Amen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
